@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Tri" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 4 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click (with the left mouse button) on a tile and hold the
mouse button until you get to the tile where you want to move the
link(s). The following illustrations show the permitted moves:

             o   o        o   *        o - o
            /       ->   /       ->       /
           * - o        o - o        o   o


              o           o            o
             /           /              +
            *   o   ->  o   *    ->  o   o
             +           +              /
              o           o            o


              *           o            o
             / +         / +
            o   o   ->  o   o    ->  o   o
                                      + /
              o           *            o


             * - o        o - o        o   o
            /       ->   /       ->       /
           o   o        o   *        o - o

...of course, the opposite moves are allowed :)

@{b}Note@{ub}: -The '*' represents the tiles clicked at the start and the end
       of a move.
      -The 'o' are the other tiles from the board.
      -The '-', '/' and '+' represent the links between the tiles.

Prohibited moves:

  A link cannot be placed on another:

             o - *         o - o         o   o
                /   ->        /    ->   /
           o - o         * - o         o = o
                                         ^
                                         Two links

  A link cannot be extended:

           o   o          o   o          o   o
            +              +            /
         o   * - o  ->  *   o - o  ->  o - o - o
                /              /              /
           o   o          o   o          o   o

 ...Anyway, the game will check if a move is permitted and if it
is, Tri will move the link(s) accordingly.

  Note that you cannot move the links to a tile already connected by
other links. However, you can link together the two ends of the
chain. But beware, because once they are 'glued' together, they
cannot be unglued... so connect these ends only when you are about
to match the pattern shown on the upper right, otherwise the game
may be impossible to complete.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button
(or with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

  The colour of the links can be changed by clicking on the pattern
to match.

  Have fun!

